  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.",
    "Add chopped onion and minced garlic, sauté for about 3 minutes until softened.",
    "Gradually add lamb mince to the pan, breaking it up with a wooden spoon.",
    "Season with red pepper flakes, salt, and freshly ground black pepper as desired. Stir occasionally for about 5-7 minutes or until the mixture turns brown.",
    "Remove from heat and add chopped basil leaves. Mix well to combine.",
    "Serve hot over steamed vegetables or rice."
